new Path(\"/\")}}. {{new Path(\"/\").isRoot()}} equals true. This is OK.\n\nThe behavior for relative path is misreading. {{new Path(\"..\").getParent()}} equals {{new Path(\".\")}}.  {{new Path(\".\").isRoot()}} always return true in the current implementation.\n\nA Path class object doesn't know the working directory. It can not say whether it repesents the root directory for relative path.\n\nJust seeing the method name and the comment, I misunderstood it returns true iif the path is \"/\". ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=fjk","name":"fjk","key":"fjk","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Kazuho Fujii","active":true,"timeZone":"Asia/Tokyo"},"created":"2015-11-04T01:12:42.264+0000","updated":"2015-11-04T01:12:42.264+0000"}],"maxResults":3,"total":3,"startAt":0},"votes":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/HADOOP-12543/votes","votes":0,"hasVoted":false},"worklog":{"startAt":0,"maxResults":20,"total":0,"worklogs":[]},"customfield_12311820":"0|i2nv1r:"}}